<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=8834'><h3>View taxon page for Ceanothus</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#ACT1'">1.</a><a name="ACT1."> </a> Stipules knob-like, corky, thick, bases persistent; leaves generally opposite (generally alternate in <I>Ceanothus megacarpus</I> var. <I>megacarpus</I>, <I>Ceanothus verrucosus</I>), clustered or not; inflorescence generally umbel-like (subg. <I>Cerastes</I>)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#ACT2'">2.</a><a name="ACT2."> </a> Leaves generally alternate

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#ACT3'">3.</a><a name="ACT3."> </a> Leaf blade 10&ndash;25 mm, 5&ndash;12 mm wide, length generally > 2 &times; width, elliptic to widely oblanceolate, margin entire; fruit 7&ndash;12 mm wide <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=75444">.....&nbsp;C. megacarpus var. megacarpus</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#ACT3.">3'</a><a name="ACT3'"> </a> Leaf blade 5&ndash;14 mm, 3&ndash;10 mm wide, length generally &lt; 2 &times; width, widely obovate to round, margin entire or teeth &plusmn; sharp; fruit 4&ndash;6 mm wide <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18506">.....&nbsp;C. verrucosus</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#ACT2.">2'</a><a name="ACT2'"> </a> Leaves generally opposite, occasionally clustered

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#ACT4'">4.</a><a name="ACT4."> </a> Plant mat- to mound-like, generally &lt; 1 m; stems spreading, &plusmn; ascending, occasionally arched, rooting at nodes or not

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#ACT5'">5.</a><a name="ACT5."> </a> Leaf margin generally entire, occasionally &plusmn; 3&ndash;5-toothed distally

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#ACT6'">6.</a><a name="ACT6."> </a> Leaf blade 8&ndash;20 mm, gray-tomentose abaxially, margin thick or &plusmn; rolled under; Central Coast (nw San Luis Obispo Co.), &lt; 60 m <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18469">.....&nbsp;C. maritimus</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#ACT6.">6'</a><a name="ACT6'"> </a> Leaf blade generally 4&ndash;12 mm, &plusmn; glabrous to strigose abaxially, margin not thick, &plusmn; not rolled under; Klamath Ranges, n North Coast Ranges, n&c Sierra Nevada, > 260 m

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#ACT7'">7.</a><a name="ACT7."> </a> Leaves generally clustered, generally erect <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18494">.....&nbsp;C. roderickii</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#ACT7.">7'</a><a name="ACT7'"> </a> Leaves &plusmn; evenly spaced, generally not clustered, spreading to ascending

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#ACT8'">8.</a><a name="ACT8."> </a> Plant generally mound-like, generally 0.3&ndash;1 m, stems not rooting at nodes; twigs brown to gray-brown <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=86346">.....&nbsp;C. arcuatus</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#ACT8.">8'</a><a name="ACT8'"> </a> Plant mat-like, &lt; 0.3 m, stems rooting at nodes; twigs generally red-brown <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18448">.....&nbsp;C. fresnensis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#ACT5.">5'</a><a name="ACT5'"> </a> Leaf blade margin 2&ndash;35-toothed

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#ACT9'">9.</a><a name="ACT9."> </a> Leaf blade generally wide-elliptic or -obovate or round, length generally &lt; 2 &times; width;, margin 5&ndash;35-toothed

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#ACT10'">10.</a><a name="ACT10."> </a> Twigs generally not angled; flowers white to pale blue or blue-lavender

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#ACT11'">11.</a><a name="ACT11."> </a> Leaf blade 10&ndash;20 mm; fruit 6&ndash;9 mm wide; horns 1&ndash;2 mm, wrinkled; Klamath Ranges (Trinity Mtns), s High Sierra Nevada (Kern Plateau), 1050&ndash;2750 m <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18488">.....&nbsp;C. pinetorum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#ACT11.">11'</a><a name="ACT11'"> </a> Leaf blade 4&ndash;10 mm; fruit 4&ndash;6 mm wide; horns &lt; 1 mm, smooth; Central Coast, &lt; 400 m <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18436">.....&nbsp;C. rigidus</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#ACT10.">10'</a><a name="ACT10'"> </a> Twigs generally angled distally; flowers blue to blue-purple <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18449">.....&nbsp;C. gloriosus</a>

